latestPosts.caption:
Today was one of those perfect, slow Sundays at home. We woke up early to the nicest weather, so the first thing we did was make CHAI and sit out on the patio. My husband, mother-in-law and I spent the morning just talking-nothing too serious, just fun conversations about everything and nothing!

Lunch was a treat, my mother-in-law made her Mutton Rogan Josh, and it was as divine as ever! After lunch, my husband and I curled up to watch How I Met Your Mother (his all-time favorite). That, of course, turned into a nap, which we didn’t even realize we needed.

When I woke up, all I could think about was coffee! Naturally, I bugged my husband to make me one and as always, he nailed it. ☕️ 

Here’s the recipe if you want to try it:
	•	1 tbsp coffee (Nescafe Black Roast or Davidoff Rich Aroma)
	•	1.5 tbsp sugar (or 2 if you like it sweeter!)
	•	2-3 drops of vanilla essence
	•	A pinch of salt
	•	Half a cup of water (froth it for 4 minutes)
	•	3-4 ice cubes + 2 small cups of milk

Sipping coffee, we spent some time playing fetch with the dogs in the garden—it was such a happy, wholesome moment. Later, I cleaned my room (feeling a little productive!) and now, while you’re reading this, I’m probably eating homemade pani puri and bhel! 

I love days like this-simple, cozy, and full of love. 💕 How did you spend your Sunday? Let me know in the comments!
